1
00:01:38,966 --> 00:01:41,588
[Episode 2]

2
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,359
Xing Wu! I...

3
00:01:47,359 --> 00:01:48,920
What's wrong?

4
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,719
There are bugs.

5
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,799
Bugs?

6
00:01:52,799 --> 00:01:54,988
So many big bugs!

7
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,439
Did you see them?

8
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,599
There are no big bugs.

9
00:02:02,599 --> 00:02:03,760
There are so many!

10
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,439
Is it this one?

11
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:08,619
Don't come over here! Stay back!

12
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,280
What's the big deal?

13
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,599
Just let it go?

14
00:02:13,599 --> 00:02:14,960
Screaming so loudly,

15
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,280
you've scared off all its friends.

16
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,439
It's fine.

17
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:20,599
You'll get used to it after a few times.

18
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,234
Hurry up and wash up.

19
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,899
It's so hot.

20
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:49,120
Aren't you hot?

21
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,520
There's a sea breeze outside.

22
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,360
And a fan inside.

23
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,160
I'm not hot.

24
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,199
An air conditioner is much cooler.

25
00:03:01,199 --> 00:03:02,439
Why don't you install one?

26
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:04,939
A calm mind keeps you cool.

27
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,319
If you're so hot,

28
00:03:07,319 --> 00:03:08,455
take the fan.

29
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:11,280
Well, a used air conditioner
shouldn't cost much, right?

30
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:14,000
How about this?
Let's split the cost and buy one.

31
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,363
That way, after I leave, you can still use it.

32
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:18,182
It's a win-win.

33
00:03:21,435 --> 00:03:23,319
I think that's a great idea.

34
00:03:23,319 --> 00:03:24,879
Given the conditions in Zhazhating,

35
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:26,199
if you're so rich,

36
00:03:26,199 --> 00:03:28,319
you can install one in every house.

37
00:03:28,319 --> 00:03:29,680
Benefit the whole town.

38
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,480
How about that?

39
00:03:57,240 --> 00:04:00,080
Are you going to sleep?

40
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,360
You're not sleeping?

41
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:04,439
Your mom said you wouldn't be back to sleep.

42
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:06,759
You believe everything my mom says?

43
00:04:06,759 --> 00:04:09,120
No, I mean...

44
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:12,100
Are you planning to sleep here tonight?

45
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:33,120
You're not really planning
to sleep here, are you?

46
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:35,300
I think the two of us...

47
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,460
What about us?

48
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:42,059
It's not appropriate for us to share a room.

49
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,220
I agree.

50
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,319
Are you asleep?

51
00:05:21,319 --> 00:05:22,439
How are you feeling?

52
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,379
Are you adjusting okay?

53
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:34,179
Land, die, box. It's a total disaster.

54
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:41,214
Feels like you've jumped back 20 years in time.

55
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,860
I'll go abroad once this month is over.

56
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,160
By the way, did you send the package?

57
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,360
Here's the tracking number and photo.

58
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,399
I sent it via express. Keep an eye out for it.

59
00:05:54,399 --> 00:05:56,904
Also, you need to record a video
for your course application.

60
00:05:56,904 --> 00:05:57,991
Don't forget.

61
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:59,199
If you need any help,

62
00:05:59,199 --> 00:06:01,259
I'm always here.

63
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,600
Actually, the moment I got here,

64
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,179
I wanted to go back to Beijing.

65
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:12,238
But it's pretty hard for you
to go back to Beijing now, right?

66
00:06:43,274 --> 00:06:46,579
Wu, how's it going with our cousin?

67
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:49,879
A girl from the big city

68
00:06:49,879 --> 00:06:52,160
is really something else.

69
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,819
Wash up and go to bed.

70
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,240
Coming!

71
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:11,240
Sweet tofu pudding, millet porridge,
and pickles.

72
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,300
Sit by the window.

73
00:08:14,079 --> 00:08:16,199
For breakfast: buns, wontons,
youtiao and tofu curd.

74
00:08:16,199 --> 00:08:18,279
- Your pick?
- A large bowl of three-flavor wontons.

75
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:19,959
- With seaweed and dried shrimp.
- Auntie Jin!

76
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,439
- Auntie Jin!
- Seaweed and dried shrimp.

77
00:08:21,439 --> 00:08:23,560
My mom sent me to buy
pork and cabbage dumplings.

78
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,439
- Thirty of them.
- Thirty. Got it.

79
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:27,540
Okay, I'll pick them up at noon.

80
00:08:29,710 --> 00:08:31,279
Hey, dear.

81
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:33,039
Did Hu take his medicine?

82
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:35,787
No. He said it's too bitter.

83
00:08:35,787 --> 00:08:37,120
If you want to be the best,

84
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,639
you have to endure the worst.

85
00:08:38,639 --> 00:08:41,120
If he can't take this,
how can he cure his stutter?

86
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,960
But the book says
all medicine is part poison, right?

87
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:46,159
- Can't count on you. I'll handle it myself.
- Selling...

88
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:48,695
Selling tofu!

89
00:08:49,662 --> 00:08:50,840
You're really something.

90
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,120
- What's up?
- Look at you!

91
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,879
- I'm riding here!
- Move! Everyone, move!

92
00:08:54,879 --> 00:08:57,720
Why is this so... How did you walk into me?

93
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:58,759
Hurry up!

94
00:08:58,759 --> 00:09:00,519
Hurry up!

95
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:03,300
Pay up now! Pay and we're done.

96
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:05,679
- You can't even walk?
- Look at this!

97
00:09:05,679 --> 00:09:06,759
Pay up now!

98
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:08,399
Pay up to settle it!

99
00:09:08,399 --> 00:09:12,159
Pay up! Pay up!
You're not leaving until you pay!

100
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:14,519
What's all the noise so early?

101
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:18,240
You're disturbing me.
I can call the police, you know?

102
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,399
She...

103
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:20,759
She said she's calling the police.

104
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:23,200
- Arrest who?
- This girl is from the big city.

105
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:25,279
She's got a bigger temper than you all.

106
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:26,279
Break it up! Scatter!

107
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:28,039
That won't do. This tofu can't be sold now.

108
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:30,740
I'll buy all your tofu.

109
00:09:53,327 --> 00:09:55,120
It hurts!

110
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,879
What's wrong?

111
00:09:56,879 --> 00:09:58,979
I didn't see it.

112
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,600
- What happened?
- Wait! Don't!

113
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,799
I haven't touched you yet.

114
00:10:02,799 --> 00:10:03,919
Help her up. Help her up.

115
00:10:03,919 --> 00:10:05,519
I didn't touch you, yet you're crying out.

116
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:07,960
My foot, my foot!

117
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,840
Easy. Take it easy!

118
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,200
- I'm being easy.
- It hurts.

119
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,279
- Hang in there. Anywhere else?
- Get up for a second.

120
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,879
- Slowly.
- Okay.

121
00:10:14,879 --> 00:10:16,000
Take it easy, take it easy.

122
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:18,120
It really, really hurts.

123
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,279
Okay, okay. Slowly, slowly.

124
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:22,260
Can't bend over.

125
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:27,380
Where'd you get hurt?

126
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,120
It's killing me.

127
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,360
- It hurts so much.
- Ye.

128
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,734
Your eyes...

129
00:10:33,734 --> 00:10:35,840
They look like the 2-dot tile.

130
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,640
I...

131
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,600
What's wrong with my eyes?

132
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,440
How did this happen?

133
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,759
Don't touch it with your hands.

134
00:10:44,759 --> 00:10:46,080
This...

135
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,600
- What's going on?
- Well, your eyes

136
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,399
probably got bitten by mosquitoes.

137
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:51,320
This side looks like an allergic reaction.

138
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,240
What should I do?

139
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,759
Why can't I see clearly now?

140
00:10:54,759 --> 00:10:55,879
I used to see just fine.

141
00:10:55,879 --> 00:10:57,440
I'm not going blind, am I?

142
00:10:57,440 --> 00:11:00,000
Just shut up. My house isn't that toxic.
You won't go blind.

143
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,080
Then what do we do now?

144
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,840
It's okay. Let's get you to the clinic.

145
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,200
But... My ID is still upstairs.

146
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,879
- Stop rubbing it.
- You just need to show up.

147
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:08,960
- Right.
- Then I...

148
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,279
I have to go up and change.

149
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:12,240
I can't go out in my PJs. So embarrassing.

150
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,360
Out on the street.

151
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,399
- Change for what? No one here cares.
- Exactly.

152
00:11:15,399 --> 00:11:16,919
Then... How about this, Auntie?

153
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,159
Get me my sunglasses.

154
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:19,639
S-Sunglasses...

155
00:11:19,639 --> 00:11:22,380
What sunglasses? You're already blind.

156
00:11:49,399 --> 00:11:50,519
Put me down!

157
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:52,120
This is so embarrassing.

158
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,679
Just cover your face.
Then no one will recognize you.

159
00:11:54,679 --> 00:11:57,339
Help! I really...

160
00:12:06,519 --> 00:12:07,639
Put me down!

161
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:08,759
Dr. Zhuang!

162
00:12:08,759 --> 00:12:09,919
Someone's dying!

163
00:12:09,919 --> 00:12:11,600
You're the one who's dying.

164
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,759
Is this tiny clinic really okay?

165
00:12:13,759 --> 00:12:17,120
In Zhazhating,
this is the first-class hospital.

166
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,279
I want to go to a real first-class hospital.

167
00:12:19,279 --> 00:12:20,360
Fine.

168
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,759
Five minutes to the bus stop,

169
00:12:21,759 --> 00:12:22,960
40 minutes on the bus,

170
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,320
then another twenty-minute walk.

171
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,440
Like 30 or 40 kilometers.

172
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,519
Go there yourself.

173
00:12:26,519 --> 00:12:29,039
You're lying.

174
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:31,519
Princess, stop being so dramatic.

175
00:12:31,519 --> 00:12:34,099
This is just how it is in Zhazhating.

176
00:12:39,399 --> 00:12:41,200
It's so early.

177
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,120
What's wrong? Who's dying?

178
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:46,120
- Her. She's dying.
- You're dying.

179
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,360
Nonsense. What's wrong with you?

180
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:50,399
Please, take a look.

181
00:12:50,399 --> 00:12:52,759
She's going blind and her leg is broken.

182
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:54,600
This...

183
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,979
More nonsense.

184
00:12:58,399 --> 00:13:00,120
Come on, let me see.

185
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,459
Open your eyes. Let me see.

186
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,260
Open them up.

187
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,720
Come on, open up.

188
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,960
Look up.

189
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,000
Look down.

190
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,120
Look left.

191
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,200
Doctor,

192
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,519
is just looking enough?

193
00:13:15,519 --> 00:13:18,120
Shouldn't I have a blood test, an X-ray,

194
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,240
or a CT scan or something?

195
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,519
No need.

196
00:13:20,519 --> 00:13:21,960
Your right eye...

197
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,639
is from sleeping on it.

198
00:13:23,639 --> 00:13:26,380
And a mosquito bit your left eye.

199
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:30,740
What did I tell you?

200
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,960
Then... how should it be treated?

201
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:36,960
Just use some eye drops and it'll be fine.

202
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:39,240
No shots, pills, or anti-inflammatories?

203
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,720
Why shots?

204
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,840
Why pills?

205
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,960
You young people don't act

206
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,039
like you're a patient.

207
00:13:44,039 --> 00:13:47,339
Remember, don't rub your eyes for a few days.

208
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:49,519
Wait a minute, Doctor.

209
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:52,320
My leg is hurt too. Who'll check that?

210
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,639
- Your leg is hurt too?
- Yes.

211
00:13:53,639 --> 00:13:55,320
Let me see.

212
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,403
W-Wait. Still you?

213
00:13:57,403 --> 00:13:59,879
Don't I need an X-ray first?

214
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:01,840
I have to look at it first.

215
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,080
Whether it swims, flies,
or walks on the ground,

216
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,279
Dr. Zhuang can treat it.

217
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:08,639
He even saved two poisoned wolfhounds.

218
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,559
Is he a doctor or a vet?

219
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:12,600
Don't listen to him.

220
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:14,600
I got a license.

221
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,740
Come on, let me see.

222
00:14:17,519 --> 00:14:20,020
It hurts!

223
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,600
This right here...

224
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,799
You just bumped it by accident.

225
00:14:27,799 --> 00:14:29,879
Just a surface wound. Bone's fine.

226
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:31,320
But it hurts!

227
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,960
Don't I need an X-ray
to know if the bone is fine?

228
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,000
If I say it's fine, it's fine.

229
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,679
You just bumped it.

230
00:14:37,679 --> 00:14:38,759
Be careful for a few days.

231
00:14:38,759 --> 00:14:40,000
Don't walk around too much.

232
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,120
Apply some iodine and ointment,

233
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:44,240
and you'll be fine.

234
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:47,339
Come on, Wu. Come get the medicine with me.

235
00:14:57,399 --> 00:15:00,600
Who is this girl to you?

236
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,440
A real piece of work.

237
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,360
There you go again.

238
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,639
She's my cousin.

239
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:06,919
It's her first time here,

240
00:15:06,919 --> 00:15:10,000
so she makes a fuss over everything.

241
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,039
Here's the girl's medicine.

242
00:15:12,039 --> 00:15:14,939
Change the dressing every twelve hours.

243
00:15:15,519 --> 00:15:17,720
Here's your grandma's meds for the month.

244
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,919
Herbal meds, oral.

245
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,200
Ointment, external.

246
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,519
That's it.

247
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:23,080
Got it. Thanks, Dr. Zhuang.

248
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:24,320
Go on.

249
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:26,900
Help the girl apply the ointment.

250
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,519
Come on, put your foot up.

251
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:39,159
What are you doing?

252
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:40,240
Applying the ointment.

253
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,200
The doctor won't do it?

254
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,360
Young lady, don't act like a helpless patient.

255
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,579
You'll have to do it yourself at home.

256
00:15:47,519 --> 00:15:49,339
Put it up.

257
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,660
It hurts.

258
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:42,353
Hold on. What is this?

259
00:16:44,159 --> 00:16:46,200
It doesn't even have a label or a permit.

260
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,679
Is it safe to use?

261
00:16:47,679 --> 00:16:49,559
Dr. Zhuang's secret ointment.

262
00:16:49,559 --> 00:16:51,519
Specially for sprains and bruises.

263
00:16:51,519 --> 00:16:53,319
It works.

264
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,639
All done.

265
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:35,540
Don't we have to pay?

266
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,839
No need.

267
00:17:37,839 --> 00:17:39,599
Put it on my tab.

268
00:17:39,599 --> 00:17:41,740
You can have a tab here?

269
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:43,759
That's how we do it here.

270
00:17:43,759 --> 00:17:46,659
Not just a tab, we pay monthly.

271
00:17:48,279 --> 00:17:49,839
Let's add each other on WeChat.

272
00:17:49,839 --> 00:17:52,180
I'll pay you for the medicine.

273
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:56,799
If you don't want to add me, fine.

274
00:17:56,799 --> 00:17:58,119
Next time I need you,

275
00:17:58,119 --> 00:17:59,920
I'll just shout for you.

276
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:02,319
Fine, let's add each other.

277
00:18:02,319 --> 00:18:05,000
While you're at it, cover my fare too.

278
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,099
One yuan per step.

279
00:18:10,599 --> 00:18:12,399
There.

280
00:18:24,039 --> 00:18:26,359
- Let's go.
- Dr. Zhuang said

281
00:18:26,359 --> 00:18:28,819
I should avoid walking.

282
00:18:34,799 --> 00:18:36,599
Come on.

283
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:40,339
One yuan per step is too expensive.

284
00:18:42,319 --> 00:18:44,339
Going back is free.

285
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,640
Hurry up, hurry up.

286
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:52,499
Don't let everyone see me like this.

287
00:18:52,499 --> 00:18:54,359
Hurry up.

288
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:58,260
On purpose? Are you going or not?

289
00:19:00,319 --> 00:19:01,400
Hurry.

290
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,460
Xing Wu!

291
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,799
- Wu.
- Good morning, madam.

292
00:19:05,799 --> 00:19:09,039
- What's going on here?
- This... Ye, what happened to your eyes?

293
00:19:09,039 --> 00:19:11,119
And what happened to your foot?

294
00:19:11,119 --> 00:19:15,053
I got bitten in the eye, sprained my foot.

295
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,880
- Be careful.
- I'll take her back now.

296
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:20,559
- Hurry up.
- Rest up and get well.

297
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:23,119
You've got the medicine, so take it.

298
00:19:23,119 --> 00:19:25,079
My goodness. Look at this girl.

299
00:19:25,079 --> 00:19:27,240
Yesterday when she got here,
she was all dressed up.

300
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,160
Today, she's out in her pajamas,

301
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,319
letting Xing Wu carry her.

302
00:19:30,319 --> 00:19:31,839
Exactly.

303
00:19:31,839 --> 00:19:33,799
She adapts pretty fast.

304
00:19:33,799 --> 00:19:35,440
You have no idea. This morning,

305
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,799
she was shouting just like Fang.

306
00:19:36,799 --> 00:19:38,920
Yelling at the top of her lungs.
Totally fierce.

307
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,240
Really?

308
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:41,240
She's one of us now.

309
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,599
She's just going native.

310
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:44,343
True.

311
00:19:44,343 --> 00:19:45,680
- You're back.
- Mom.

312
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:48,280
- Here, here.
- Come on.

313
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,500
Careful.

314
00:19:53,519 --> 00:19:54,519
Give this to me.

315
00:19:54,519 --> 00:19:56,400
Come on.

316
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,000
Up you go.

317
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,800
Good.

318
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,440
What did Dr. Zhuang say?

319
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,880
Dr. Zhuang's clinic can't handle her case.

320
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,160
Needs a real hospital in the city.

321
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:14,119
She might even need surgery.

322
00:20:14,119 --> 00:20:16,540
Amputation's not off the table.

323
00:20:17,279 --> 00:20:19,200
That serious?

324
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,799
It's all your fault.

325
00:20:20,799 --> 00:20:23,880
- Well...
- Why not look after your cousin better?

326
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,119
Ye, I'm so sorry.

327
00:20:25,119 --> 00:20:26,759
It's not that serious.

328
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:28,960
Don't listen to his nonsense.

329
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:32,339
Just some eye drops and ointment,
and I'll be fine.

330
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,039
That's a relief.

331
00:20:36,039 --> 00:20:37,400
I'm glad it's not that serious.

332
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,079
Then make sure you use the eye drops.

333
00:20:39,079 --> 00:20:40,799
And apply the ointment properly.

334
00:20:40,799 --> 00:20:42,960
I went next door especially

335
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:45,279
to buy you buns and fried dough sticks.

336
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:47,359
And I made you pork trotter soup.

337
00:20:47,359 --> 00:20:49,619
Eat what you hurt to heal it.

338
00:20:51,079 --> 00:20:52,940
It's okay.

339
00:20:54,288 --> 00:20:56,108
I'm not hungry.

340
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,880
Don't worry about the final payment.

341
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:02,200
It's not about the money.

342
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,200
I'm just...

343
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,460
I'm just glad you're okay.

344
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,279
I'm full.

345
00:21:09,279 --> 00:21:11,180
I'm heading to Shunyi.

346
00:21:11,839 --> 00:21:14,740
Okay, be careful on the road.

347
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:20,240
What do you want for lunch?

348
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,319
I'll cook for you.

349
00:21:22,319 --> 00:21:24,500
I haven't decided yet.

350
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:31,279
Why don't you order from next door?

351
00:21:31,279 --> 00:21:33,500
Their food is good.

352
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:36,720
I'll be at the Mahjong Club.

353
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,960
Play some mahjong.

354
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,799
Just shout if you need anything.

355
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:40,839
I'll hear you.

356
00:21:40,839 --> 00:21:43,300
Okay. I understand.

357
00:21:44,039 --> 00:21:46,619
I'll just go now.

358
00:22:29,416 --> 00:22:32,557
[Shunyi Repairs]

359
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,519
The repairs are done.

360
00:22:49,519 --> 00:22:51,839
Tell the owners to come pick them up.

361
00:22:51,839 --> 00:22:53,400
That was fast.

362
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:56,039
Wu, you really don't want to
partner up at Shunyi?

363
00:22:56,039 --> 00:22:57,400
With our skills,

364
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,240
we could dominate Anzi County.

365
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:03,115
Shunyi only needs one boss, and that's you.

366
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,519
True.

367
00:23:05,519 --> 00:23:06,759
So many people in Zhazhating

368
00:23:06,759 --> 00:23:08,940
are still counting on you.

369
00:23:14,960 --> 00:23:16,559
Canine.

370
00:23:16,559 --> 00:23:18,440
Send any work you have my way lately.

371
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,440
Anything is fine.

372
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,519
House calls too.

373
00:23:21,519 --> 00:23:22,559
Are you short on cash?

374
00:23:22,559 --> 00:23:23,960
Always.

375
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:26,759
You can never have enough money.

376
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:27,960
What a coincidence.

377
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:30,899
This morning, a big spender came in.

378
00:23:31,839 --> 00:23:34,160
His phone is a brand-new model.

379
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,720
It's too new for me.

380
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:38,020
I can't fix it.

381
00:23:41,359 --> 00:23:43,220
Thanks.

382
00:23:48,799 --> 00:23:51,260
Looks like luck is on your side.

383
00:24:12,359 --> 00:24:15,559
You're Qing Ye, right?

384
00:24:15,559 --> 00:24:17,720
I've seen you when you were little.

385
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:20,419
You're all grown up now.

386
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:23,020
Grandma.

387
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,240
Grandma,

388
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,720
if you ever need any help,

389
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:27,799
just let me know.

390
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:30,160
- Okay.
- I'll be staying here for a while.

391
00:24:30,160 --> 00:24:31,599
Sorry for the trouble.

392
00:24:31,599 --> 00:24:34,899
It's fine. Thank you.

393
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:38,859
What happened to your eye?

394
00:24:40,519 --> 00:24:42,619
A mosquito bite.

395
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,319
And... you hurt your foot too?

396
00:24:46,319 --> 00:24:48,559
It's nothing. I just took a fall.

397
00:24:48,559 --> 00:24:49,920
Well...

398
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,279
Grandma.

399
00:24:51,279 --> 00:24:52,920
Grandma, let me get you some water.

400
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:55,359
Alright, alright.

401
00:24:55,359 --> 00:24:56,880
Good.

402
00:24:58,079 --> 00:25:00,240
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

403
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:03,240
You're such a good girl.

404
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,400
Well...

405
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,880
Call me if you need anything.

406
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:06,960
Okay.

407
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:09,237
- I'm going upstairs.
- Alright.

408
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:11,400
Go get some rest.

409
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,974
Okay.

410
00:25:36,119 --> 00:25:38,575
The ointment works quite well.

411
00:25:40,055 --> 00:25:43,319
[Yitong Restaurant]

412
00:25:43,319 --> 00:25:44,640
Hurry up!

413
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,400
What should I play?

414
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,400
Qing Ye is here.

415
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:50,279
Why are you out here?

416
00:25:50,279 --> 00:25:53,039
My foot is almost healed.
I came out for a stroll.

417
00:25:53,039 --> 00:25:54,920
Are you hungry?

418
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,200
Yes. I want to order food from Yitong.

419
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,880
The owner isn't there.

420
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:00,915
I'm right here.

421
00:26:01,519 --> 00:26:03,160
What would you like to eat?

422
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,920
You'd better write this down.

423
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,519
Four dishes and a soup for every meal.

424
00:26:06,519 --> 00:26:08,960
For breakfast, half the portion
and swap the soup for milk.

425
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:10,803
For each meal, at least two types of protein,

426
00:26:10,803 --> 00:26:11,970
at least two types of veggies,

427
00:26:11,970 --> 00:26:13,338
and no more than two types of carbs.

428
00:26:13,338 --> 00:26:16,365
Right. Make more food that's easy to swallow.

429
00:26:16,365 --> 00:26:18,463
And add a steamed egg with sea urchin.

430
00:26:18,463 --> 00:26:21,240
By the way, are your portions really big here?

431
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:23,720
It should be enough for two people.

432
00:26:24,365 --> 00:26:26,510
That's a lot of demands.

433
00:26:27,738 --> 00:26:30,119
It's... it's not...
I'm not taking your business.

434
00:26:30,119 --> 00:26:32,157
Look, my business here is doing just fine.

435
00:26:32,157 --> 00:26:35,916
When it's mealtime,
I'm really too busy to manage.

436
00:26:37,496 --> 00:26:40,767
Alipay received 1,000 yuan.

437
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:47,839
Even if I'm busy,
I have to prioritize you, don't I?

438
00:26:47,839 --> 00:26:50,807
This is an advance payment.
It includes labor and service fees.

439
00:26:50,807 --> 00:26:52,000
We'll square up later.

440
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,160
Okay, okay. Your health comes first.

441
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:56,238
So, what'll you have? Say that again.

442
00:26:56,238 --> 00:26:57,284
Auntie Shanxi,

443
00:26:57,284 --> 00:26:59,160
one order of mackerel dumplings to go.

444
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,480
Wait a minute.

445
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,119
How did you get back so soon?

446
00:27:02,119 --> 00:27:04,079
None of your business.

447
00:27:04,079 --> 00:27:05,160
Go on.

448
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,519
- For every meal,
- For every meal,

449
00:27:06,519 --> 00:27:09,371
- four dishes and one soup.
- four dishes and one soup.

450
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,759
Grandma.

451
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,268
Grandma, time to eat.

452
00:27:18,904 --> 00:27:21,612
I'm not hungry yet.

453
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:25,279
Where did you go just now?

454
00:27:25,279 --> 00:27:27,079
Grandma,

455
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:30,400
I took Qing Ye to see the doctor this morning,

456
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,599
so I couldn't bring you food.

457
00:27:32,599 --> 00:27:34,759
These are dumplings Auntie Shanxi made for you.

458
00:27:34,759 --> 00:27:35,839
Here, have a taste.

459
00:27:35,839 --> 00:27:37,440
Okay.

460
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,920
Here.

461
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,528
The vinegar smells good.

462
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,720
It's delicious.

463
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:45,640
Let me tell you something.

464
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,000
Now,

465
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,680
it's not just you being filial anymore.

466
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:53,558
I've got an extra granddaughter now,
looking after me.

467
00:27:59,279 --> 00:28:02,119
Fruit! Fruit!

468
00:28:02,119 --> 00:28:04,680
Tofu!

469
00:28:04,680 --> 00:28:07,039
Fruit! Fruit!

470
00:28:07,039 --> 00:28:09,644
Tofu!

471
00:28:11,425 --> 00:28:13,119
Wu!

472
00:28:13,119 --> 00:28:14,319
Liu Nian.

473
00:28:14,319 --> 00:28:15,960
Why are you coming out of Grandma's room?

474
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,359
I'm doing housekeeping.

475
00:28:17,359 --> 00:28:18,440
Housekeeping?

476
00:28:18,440 --> 00:28:19,720
Just helping Grandma

477
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:22,227
dust and clean her room.

478
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,759
Housekeeping is fine.

479
00:28:24,759 --> 00:28:25,880
Just don't disturb Grandma.

480
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,919
Don't worry, no problem.

481
00:29:06,759 --> 00:29:08,119
In a small place like that,

482
00:29:08,119 --> 00:29:09,519
as long as the money is right,

483
00:29:09,519 --> 00:29:11,359
everything is easy.

484
00:29:11,359 --> 00:29:14,407
Why didn't he take the money?

485
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,599
Cousin!

486
00:29:34,599 --> 00:29:37,319
Stop yelling. I'm not your cousin.

487
00:29:37,319 --> 00:29:39,200
Hey, don't be like that.

488
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:41,295
First time's a stranger, second time's family.

489
00:29:41,295 --> 00:29:42,599
I'm actually a pretty good guy.

490
00:29:42,599 --> 00:29:44,383
You just need to get to know me.

491
00:29:44,383 --> 00:29:47,264
Oh, right. I saw your package at the station.
Grabbed it for you.

492
00:29:47,264 --> 00:29:49,799
Okay, thank you.

493
00:29:49,799 --> 00:29:51,920
Don't mention it.

494
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,925
Wu's cousin is my cousin too.

495
00:29:53,925 --> 00:29:56,720
Whatever you need, just say the word.

496
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:59,519
Where else sells fruit around here?
I want some fruit.

497
00:29:59,519 --> 00:30:01,335
Of course there are. Look,

498
00:30:01,335 --> 00:30:03,495
we have plenty of local produce.
We have all kinds of fruit.

499
00:30:03,495 --> 00:30:04,839
What do you want? I'll get it.

500
00:30:04,839 --> 00:30:07,559
I want avocados and cherries.

501
00:30:07,559 --> 00:30:09,799
- Can't get them?
- No way.

502
00:30:09,799 --> 00:30:11,843
Let me tell you,
even if they're at the North Pole,

503
00:30:11,843 --> 00:30:14,166
I'll dive in and swim there
to bring them back for you.

504
00:30:14,166 --> 00:30:15,247
QR code for payment.

505
00:30:15,247 --> 00:30:17,253
No need.

506
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:38,517
Thanks, I've received it all.

507
00:30:39,905 --> 00:30:42,942
Get ready for school
over the next couple of days.

508
00:30:48,079 --> 00:30:50,799
Can you keep a low profile
since you're new here?

509
00:30:50,799 --> 00:30:53,037
How am I being high-profile?

510
00:30:54,079 --> 00:30:55,559
Flaunting your wealth as soon as you arrive.

511
00:30:55,559 --> 00:30:57,279
Around here, it's not like your big city.

512
00:30:57,279 --> 00:30:58,640
Be careful not to get targeted.

513
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:00,559
How am I flaunting wealth?

514
00:31:00,559 --> 00:31:02,359
I wasn't showing off.

515
00:31:02,359 --> 00:31:05,599
I'm just spending money on services.

516
00:31:05,599 --> 00:31:08,599
Besides, don't people here love money?

517
00:31:08,599 --> 00:31:10,079
Thanks for the warning,

518
00:31:10,079 --> 00:31:12,798
but how I spend my money is my business.

519
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,161
Suit yourself.

520
00:31:35,359 --> 00:31:38,880
Hi, everyone.
I'm so glad to introduce myself here.

521
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:40,599
- My name is...
- Xing Wu!

522
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:43,145
Are you out of your mind?

523
00:31:44,839 --> 00:31:47,556
Xing Wu, come out here!

524
00:31:50,677 --> 00:31:53,117
Did you change that door lock?

525
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:58,000
Why should we be the ones to change it?

526
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,640
It's already installed.
It's not like I asked you for money.

527
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:03,559
The girl needs to shower.
What if someone peeps at her?

528
00:32:03,559 --> 00:32:05,960
Have you lost your mind?

529
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:08,799
I've showered here for so many years.
Who has ever peeped?

530
00:32:08,799 --> 00:32:11,200
Besides, what do you mean by
"not ask me for money"?

531
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:14,880
Is that how you talk to me?
Isn't your money our family's money?

532
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,960
- How much was that lock?
- Wait, what are you doing?

533
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:19,039
I'm going to make them split the cost.

534
00:32:19,039 --> 00:32:20,920
Is that really necessary?

535
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:23,319
You spent hundreds on clothes
without batting an eye.

536
00:32:23,319 --> 00:32:24,920
It's just a lock.

537
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,000
Yes, it is! It is! It is!

538
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,079
The showerhead, the water heater,
the light bulbs...

539
00:32:29,079 --> 00:32:31,319
Our family's replaced the most of them.

540
00:32:31,319 --> 00:32:33,519
Do they ever show us any gratitude?

541
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:34,599
Last winter,

542
00:32:34,599 --> 00:32:36,359
Wu Lao Er found a scrap wire

543
00:32:36,359 --> 00:32:38,200
and put it in our yard
to use as a clothesline.

544
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,839
Then, just for ten yuan,
he hounded me for a month.

545
00:32:40,839 --> 00:32:44,831
Why's it always us paying?
Why is it always us?

546
00:32:44,831 --> 00:32:46,697
How much?

547
00:32:47,655 --> 00:32:49,000
W-What?

548
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,079
How much for the lock?

549
00:32:50,079 --> 00:32:51,359
I'll pay.

550
00:32:51,359 --> 00:32:52,880
Is five hundred enough?

551
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:55,593
Wait... Qing Ye.

552
00:32:57,079 --> 00:32:58,319
I didn't mean for you to...

553
00:32:58,319 --> 00:33:02,079
Alipay received 500 yuan.

554
00:33:02,079 --> 00:33:05,295
It's just a lock.
Is it really worth all this fuss?

555
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:09,353
Just say I asked for it.

556
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,079
No.

557
00:33:13,079 --> 00:33:17,126
We didn't mean for you to pay.

558
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,000
I transferred the 500 yuan to you.

559
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:45,160
Make sure to accept it.

560
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,797
Forget it.

561
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,000
Li Lan Fang was arguing with me

562
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:58,720
because she felt the neighbors were using her.
She felt it was unfair.

563
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:01,024
It's not about the money at all.

564
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:03,160
Well, I don't care anyway.

565
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:05,790
Just think of it as me paying
for some peace and quiet.

566
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:12,066
Do you think that all of us
can be bought off with money?

567
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:16,559
- I didn't say that.
- Your actions say otherwise.

568
00:34:16,559 --> 00:34:19,146
Think whatever you want.

569
00:34:20,079 --> 00:34:21,440
To be honest,

570
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,719
your mom asked me to stay here.

571
00:34:22,719 --> 00:34:24,239
And you changed the lock for me.

572
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:26,890
Wasn't it only because I paid you?

573
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:31,537
What do you take us for?

574
00:34:32,519 --> 00:34:34,228
What do I take you for?

575
00:34:34,960 --> 00:34:37,119
Here, take a good look.

576
00:34:37,119 --> 00:34:39,280
Party A and Party B, signed and sealed.

577
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:41,321
- Look closely.
- I've never acknowledged

578
00:34:41,321 --> 00:34:42,519
a single word on this paper.

579
00:34:42,519 --> 00:34:43,639
I don't care.

580
00:34:43,639 --> 00:34:45,519
We're still Party A and Party B.

581
00:34:45,519 --> 00:34:46,639
Since I'm paying,

582
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:49,559
I deserve a quiet and comfortable environment.

583
00:34:49,559 --> 00:34:51,519
With this attitude of yours,

584
00:34:51,519 --> 00:34:54,760
I could easily refuse to pay the balance.

585
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:57,719
Do you think having money
means you can do whatever you want?

586
00:34:57,719 --> 00:35:00,559
Here for the service and a vacation, huh?
Leave right now.

587
00:35:00,559 --> 00:35:03,230
Pack your things and go to a hotel.

588
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,541
Fine, I'll leave.

589
00:35:12,179 --> 00:35:15,436
I don't want to stay in this dump
for another second!

590
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,360
- Miss, need a ride?
- Yeah.

591
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,920
Give it here.

592
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:43,245
Okay. Thank you.

593
00:35:44,311 --> 00:35:46,000
Hold on tight.

594
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,815
Sit tight.

595
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:50,079
Where are we going?

596
00:35:50,079 --> 00:35:52,360
Just keep driving straight.

597
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:55,679
Straight ahead? We'll end up in the sea.

598
00:35:55,679 --> 00:35:58,519
Then take me to the best hotel in town.

599
00:35:58,519 --> 00:36:00,300
You got it.

600
00:36:02,039 --> 00:36:04,139
Hold on.

601
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:41,234
Family dinner, a happy reunion.

602
00:36:54,208 --> 00:36:56,039
[Zhazha Grand Hotel]

603
00:36:56,039 --> 00:36:58,198
Attack him!

604
00:37:00,119 --> 00:37:02,268
Such a noob.

605
00:37:07,294 --> 00:37:09,848
Go for it, bro.

606
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:29,653
No, you go.

607
00:37:33,599 --> 00:37:35,698
Hello?

608
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:39,559
Hello!

609
00:37:39,559 --> 00:37:40,960
Hi there!

610
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:43,119
Hold on, hold on. I have a guest.

611
00:37:43,119 --> 00:37:44,840
I'd like a room.

612
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:47,461
Take your pick.

613
00:37:55,239 --> 00:37:56,559
588 yuan.

614
00:37:56,559 --> 00:37:58,320
Is that your best room?

615
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,360
Of course.

616
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:02,679
588 is our signature.
A luxury ocean-view suite.

617
00:38:02,679 --> 00:38:04,880
In all of Zhazhating,
you won't find anything better.

618
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:05,960
Got air conditioning?

619
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,719
- Of course it does.
- What about Wi-Fi?

620
00:38:07,719 --> 00:38:09,719
Wi-Fi?

621
00:38:09,719 --> 00:38:11,119
Girl,

622
00:38:11,119 --> 00:38:14,160
haven't you stayed in a hotel before?

623
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:19,498
Just check me in, please.

624
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:41,199
Air conditioning and no Xing Wu.

625
00:39:41,199 --> 00:39:44,493
I can finally get some good sleep.

626
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:54,119
Qing Ye, I checked the weather.

627
00:39:54,119 --> 00:39:56,519
Is it raining where you are?

628
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:58,760
I found some videos and courseware
for the preparatory courses.

629
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:01,079
You can watch them during summer break.

630
00:40:01,079 --> 00:40:03,392
Okay, thank you.

631
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:23,519
Wait...

632
00:40:23,519 --> 00:40:25,828
The internet is down?

633
00:40:45,279 --> 00:40:47,280
Wu!

634
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:49,168
- Coming!
- Liu Nian.

635
00:40:50,679 --> 00:40:52,880
Wu.

636
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,518
Wu.

637
00:40:54,518 --> 00:40:56,288
Wu!

638
00:40:56,920 --> 00:40:58,559
- I brought you food.
- Okay.

639
00:40:58,559 --> 00:41:00,920
This is the special meal Qing Ye ordered
from my mom.

640
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:02,996
It's enough for two people.

641
00:41:03,719 --> 00:41:05,519
Thanks.

642
00:41:05,519 --> 00:41:07,599
Well, then... Hurry up and eat.

643
00:41:07,599 --> 00:41:09,342
Okay.

644
00:41:10,070 --> 00:41:12,970
- Bye, Liu Nian.
- Bye-bye.

645
00:41:31,119 --> 00:41:33,320
Make more food that's easy to swallow.

646
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:36,039
And add a steamed egg with sea urchin.

647
00:41:36,039 --> 00:41:37,960
Are your portions really big here?

648
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:39,679
It should be enough for two people.

649
00:41:39,679 --> 00:41:42,320
You're not the only filial one.

650
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:46,795
I've got an extra granddaughter now,
looking after me.

651
00:41:53,013 --> 00:41:54,703
Wu.

652
00:41:55,559 --> 00:41:56,960
Wu.

653
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:58,416
I'm done with the cleaning.

654
00:41:58,416 --> 00:41:59,800
I'll head off now.

655
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,486
Okay.
Take an umbrella.

656
00:42:01,486 --> 00:42:04,092
- Okay.
- It's going to rain.

657
00:42:08,719 --> 00:42:11,599
Wu. I'll say one more thing.

658
00:42:11,599 --> 00:42:13,519
Actually...

659
00:42:13,519 --> 00:42:15,944
Qing Ye is quite nice.

660
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,159
Oh yeah? Did she buy you off?

661
00:42:19,159 --> 00:42:21,039
No. How is that possible?

662
00:42:21,039 --> 00:42:22,320
Here's the thing.

663
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,840
Do you want to make some extra money?

664
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:25,039
Extra money?

665
00:42:25,039 --> 00:42:26,861
What extra money?

666
00:42:26,861 --> 00:42:28,446
I just want you to help me

667
00:42:28,446 --> 00:42:32,360
clean my room upstairs and Grandma's room.
Especially Grandma's room.

668
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:34,840
Make sure you wipe away
all the dust.

669
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:36,054
Grandma is sick, you know.

670
00:42:36,054 --> 00:42:39,159
That foul air is bad for her health.

671
00:42:39,159 --> 00:42:41,955
Buy some plants for her room, too.

672
00:42:44,159 --> 00:42:46,314
I'll get going then, Wu.

673
00:43:01,446 --> 00:43:02,599
What's up?

674
00:43:02,599 --> 00:43:04,039
It's late. Have you come to your senses?

675
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:05,159
Hello, Mr. Zhu.

676
00:43:05,159 --> 00:43:07,800
Did you happen to pick up a girl
from outside my house?

677
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:10,320
Yeah. There was a girl with a suitcase.

678
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:12,199
Yes, that's her. Where did she go?

679
00:43:12,199 --> 00:43:14,792
Zhazha Grand Hotel.

680
00:43:20,719 --> 00:43:22,039
Hey, Hao.

681
00:43:22,039 --> 00:43:23,880
Is there a girl named Qing Ye

682
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:25,862
staying at your place?

683
00:43:26,559 --> 00:43:27,960
She just checked in.

684
00:43:27,960 --> 00:43:29,159
To the ocean-view suite.

685
00:43:29,159 --> 00:43:31,199
Keep an eye on her for me.

686
00:43:31,199 --> 00:43:33,639
Contact me if anything happens.

687
00:43:33,639 --> 00:43:34,760
Got it.

688
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:36,635
Thanks.
